verses.text_plain: The burden which Habakkuk the prophet did see.
verses.verse_html: 1The burden which Habakkuk the prophet did see.

verses.text_plain: O Lord, how long shall I cry, and thou wilt not hear! even cry out unto thee of violence, and thou wilt not save!
verses.verse_html: 2O Lord, how long shall I cry, and thou wilt not hear! even cry out unto thee of violence, and thou wilt not save!

verses.text_plain: Why dost thou shew me iniquity, and cause me to behold grievance? for spoiling and violence are before me: and there are that raise up strife and contention.
verses.verse_html: 3Why dost thou shew me iniquity, and cause me to behold grievance? for spoiling and violence are before me: and there are that raise up strife and contention.

verses.text_plain: Therefore the law is slacked, and judgment doth never go forth: for the wicked doth compass about the righteous; therefore wrong judgment proceedeth.
verses.verse_html:
4Therefore the law is slacked, and judgment doth never go forth: for the wicked doth compass about the righteous; therefore wrong judgment proceedeth. ▼
▼ wrong: or, wrested

verses.text_plain: Behold ye among the heathen, and regard, and wonder marvellously: for I will work a work in your days, which ye will not believe, though it be told you.
verses.verse_html: 5Behold ye among the heathen, and regard, and wonder marvellously: for I will work a work in your days, which ye will not believe, though it be told you.

verses.text_plain: For, lo, I raise up the Chaldeans, that bitter and hasty nation, which shall march through the breadth of the land, to possess the dwellingplaces that are not theirs.
verses.verse_html:
6For, lo, I raise up the Chaldeans, that bitter and hasty nation, which shall march through the breadth of the land, to possess the dwellingplaces that are not theirs. ▼
▼ breadth: Heb. breadths

verses.text_plain: They are terrible and dreadful: their judgment and their dignity shall proceed of themselves.
verses.verse_html:
7They are terrible and dreadful: their judgment and their dignity shall proceed of themselves. ▼
▼ their judgment…: or, from them shall proceed the judgment of these, and the captivity of these

footnotes.body_text: ▼ their judgment…: or, from them shall proceed the judgment of these, and the captivity of these
footnotes.body_html: ▼ their judgment…: or, from them shall proceed the judgment of these, and the captivity of these

verses.text_plain: Their horses also are swifter than the leopards, and are more fierce than the evening wolves: and their horsemen shall spread themselves, and their horsemen shall come from far; they shall fly as the eagle that hasteth to eat.
verses.verse_html:
8Their horses also are swifter than the leopards, and are more fierce than the evening wolves: and their horsemen shall spread themselves, and their horsemen shall come from far; they shall fly as the eagle that hasteth to eat. ▼
▼ fierce: Heb. sharp

verses.text_plain: They shall come all for violence: their faces shall sup up as the east wind, and they shall gather the captivity as the sand.
verses.verse_html:
9They shall come all for violence: their faces shall sup up as the east wind, and they shall gather the captivity as the sand. ▼
▼ their…: or, the supping up of their faces, etc: or, their faces shall look (Heb. the opposition of their faces) toward the east

footnotes.body_text: ▼ their…: or, the supping up of their faces, etc: or, their faces shall look (Heb. the opposition of their faces) toward the east
footnotes.body_html: ▼ their…: or, the supping up of their faces, etc: or, their faces shall look (Heb. the opposition of their faces) toward the east

verses.text_plain: And they shall scoff at the kings, and the princes shall be a scorn unto them: they shall deride every strong hold; for they shall heap dust, and take it.
verses.verse_html: 10And they shall scoff at the kings, and the princes shall be a scorn unto them: they shall deride every strong hold; for they shall heap dust, and take it.

verses.text_plain: Then shall his mind change, and he shall pass over, and offend, imputing this his power unto his god.
verses.verse_html: 11Then shall his mind change, and he shall pass over, and offend, imputing this his power unto his god.

verses.text_plain: Art thou not from everlasting, O Lord my God, mine Holy One? we shall not die. O Lord, thou hast ordained them for judgment; and, O mighty God, thou hast established them for correction.
verses.verse_html:
12Art thou not from everlasting, O Lord my God, mine Holy One? we shall not die. O Lord, thou hast ordained them for judgment; and, O mighty God, thou hast established them for correction. ▼
▼ mighty…: Heb. rock
 , ▼
▼ established: Heb. founded

verses.text_plain: Thou art of purer eyes than to behold evil, and canst not look on iniquity: wherefore lookest thou upon them that deal treacherously, and holdest thy tongue when the wicked devoureth the man that is more righteous than he?
verses.verse_html:
13Thou art of purer eyes than to behold evil, and canst not look on iniquity: wherefore lookest thou upon them that deal treacherously, and holdest thy tongue when the wicked devoureth the man that is more righteous than he? ▼
▼ iniquity: or, grievance

tokens.text: thou upon them that deal treacherously

verses.text_plain: And makest men as the fishes of the sea, as the creeping things, that have no ruler over them?
verses.verse_html:
14And makest men as the fishes of the sea, as the creeping things, that have no ruler over them? ▼
▼ creeping: or, moving

verses.text_plain: They take up all of them with the angle, they catch them in their net, and gather them in their drag: therefore they rejoice and are glad.
verses.verse_html:
15They take up all of them with the angle, they catch them in their net, and gather them in their drag: therefore they rejoice and are glad. ▼
▼ drag: or, flue net

tokens.text: all of them with the angle

footnotes.body_html: ▼ drag: or, flue net

verses.text_plain: Therefore they sacrifice unto their net, and burn incense unto their drag; because by them their portion is fat, and their meat plenteous.
verses.verse_html:
16Therefore they sacrifice unto their net, and burn incense unto their drag; because by them their portion is fat, and their meat plenteous. ▼
▼ plenteous: or, dainty: Heb. fat

footnotes.body_html: ▼ plenteous: or, dainty: Heb. fat

verses.text_plain: Shall they therefore empty their net, and not spare continually to slay the nations?
verses.verse_html: 17Shall they therefore empty their net, and not spare continually to slay the nations?
